<h1 style="text-align: center;"><strong>Anti-Bullying</strong></h1>
<h3 style="text-align: left;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">What Is Bullying:</span></h3>
<div>Bullying is aggression towards bystanders. This aggression may start with teasing or name calling but can also lead to physical and mental abuse. The more bullying is repeating the harsher it gets as they get more comfortable with it.</div>
<h3><u>What Is Cyberbullying:</u></h3>
<div>Cyberbullying is any type of bullying that can be through the internet or online. This type of bullying can be through social media apps and online messaging. If you wish to stop cyberbullying you must turn off the device immediately before it gets worse.</div>
<h3><u>How To Prevent Bullying:</u></h3>
<div dir="ltr">
<div dir="ltr">
<div>1. Always Tell An Adult</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>Sometimes telling an adult may not seem like the best option because they might bully you more because they think you're a snitch.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>2. Avoid Bullies</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>If you see a bully you should do your best to avoid them. Stay away from areas that they tend to be with so you could reduce the number of interactions you have with them.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>3. Be Around Friends</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>If a bully sees you in a group they will most likely not interact as they will find you less intimidating.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>4. Stay Confident</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>If you stay confident in front of a bully and tell them to stop they will not be as interested in bullying you.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>5.Act Immediately</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>The sooner you stop the bully the less power they have. If they keep on bullying you they will start getting more aggressive and will make you more miserable.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
</div>
</div>
